==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Algum
<hw>Al"gum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb., perh. borrowed fr. Skr.
<ets>valguka</ets> sandalwood.]</ety> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>A tree
or wood of the Bible (2 Chron. ii. 8; 1 K. x. 11).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Most writers at the present day follow Celsius, who
takes it to be the red sandalwood of China and the Indian
Archipelago.</note> <rj><au>W. Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alnage</ent>⟦br⟧
